-- Arch
fwupdate
cryptboot
exa: ls replacement
*ripgrep: fuzzy searcher - mapped in zsh to ctrl T/R
*rmtrash: trash to bin (aur)
alsa-utils: Sound config
pulseaudio: Sound server
pulseaudio-alsa: Sound server for alsa
pamixer: pulseaudio command-line mixer
iw: wifi command
fwupd: Firmware updater
*dunst: Notification service (need to figure out how to enable on boot)
*aurutils-git: Package manager for aur
*pacutils: Required by aurutils - is it needed otherwise?
*s3cmd: Used to upload packages to amazon s3

-- i3
i3-gaps
*i3status
*py3status
*i3ipc-python: An IPC for i3 using python (aur)
xorg-server
xorg-xfontsel
xorg-xinit
xorg-xprop
xorg-xrandr
rofi
rofi-calc
rofi-dmenu
kitty
terminus-font
ttf-inconsolata
otf-font-awesome: Font for icons
python-tzlocal: For status bar clock
lightdm: Login interface
lightdm-gtk-greeter: Theme for lightdm
*gsimplecal: Calendar for i3status


-- Desktop
*flameshot: screenshot tool
*compton: Some sort of compositor
*copyq: Clipboard manager
*unclutter: Hides the mouse when not in use
*ranger: File manager (can view pics in kitty)


-- Web
*vivaldi
pepper-flash
x264
*browserpass


-- Other
*pass
*usbguard

-- zsh
*antigen-git: package manager (aur)
*prezto-git: config framework (aur)
*fzy: Fuzzy text selector
lscolors-git: Colours for ls (aur)

-- Snapper
snapper: Manage btrfs snapshots
btrfs-progs: Some btrfs utilities I guess
snap-pac: Hooks for pacman to automatically create snapshots after installs
snap-pac-grub: Add grub entries every time a snapshot is made
